  "Heart: branching cells with intercalated discs and central nuclei; Biceps: long cylindrical fibers with peripheral nuclei and striations; Intestine: spindle-shaped cells with no striations": "",
  "Each muscle type has distinct microscopic features: cardiac muscle shows branching cells with central nuclei and intercalated discs; skeletal muscle shows long, multinucleated cylindrical fibers with peripheral nuclei and prominent striations; and smooth muscle shows small, spindle-shaped cells with single central nuclei and no striations.": ""
